bmpModemTable.name: bmpModemTable
bmpModemTable.description: This table contains information about all BM-P modems in all racks.

mdmRack.name: mdmRack
mdmRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed.

mdmModem.name: mdmModem
mdmModem.description: This variable displays the slot number where the corresponding modem is installed in the rack.

mdmPosition.name: mdmPosition
mdmPosition.description: This variable displays the location of the corresponding modem: 'local' or 'remote'. The modem which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

mdmModemName.name: mdmModemName
mdmModemName.description: The verbal name of this modem.

mdmDataEquipmentEmulation.name: mdmDataEquipmentEmulation
mdmDataEquipmentEmulation.description: Interface mode of the unit: 'dte' or 'dce', 'te' or 'nt'.

mdmClockMode.name: mdmClockMode
mdmClockMode.description: The clock mode of the unit: 'master' or 'slave'.

mdmDistance.name: mdmDistance
mdmDistance.description: The transmission distance of the unit: 'long' or 'short'. 'Long' is valid for link data rates of up to 64 Kbps. For data rates higher than 64 Kbps this entry must be set to 'short'.

mdmDataRateAdaptation.name: mdmDataRateAdaptation
mdmDataRateAdaptation.description: This entry enables or disables data rate adaptation, i.e. one unit operates at line speed and the other one at lower speeds (1.2, 2.4, 4.8 or 9.6 Kbps at 64 Kbps line speed and 1.2, 2.4, 4.8, 9.6 or 19.2 Kbps at 128 Kbps line speed).

mdmClockSource.name: mdmClockSource
mdmClockSource.description: The clock source of the link: 'internal', 'external', or 'async'.

mdmDataRate.name: mdmDataRate
mdmDataRate.description: The data rate at the interface in bits per seconds. If dataRateAdaptation is disabled, the data rate at the remote counterpart changes simultaneously. Otherwise the data rate at one unit is fixed to line speed and the data rate at the other unit must be set to speeds lower than line speed.

mdmLocalCarrierDetect1.name: mdmLocalCarrierDetect1
mdmLocalCarrierDetect1.description: The data carrier detect mode at the interface: if set to 'fo-link-and-remote-handshake' the DCD signal (resp. I for X.21, etc.) follows link status and remote RTS (resp. C for X.21, etc.), if set to 'fo-link' the DCD signal follows link status only.

mdmLocalCarrierDetect2.name: mdmLocalCarrierDetect2
mdmLocalCarrierDetect2.description: The data carrier detect mode 2 at the interface: if set to 'fo-link-and-remote-handshake' the DSR signal follows link status and remote RTS (resp. C for X.21, etc.), if set to 'fo-link' the DSR signal follows link status only.
